h3cVoCallHistory.name: h3cVoCallHistory

revisions.description: The initial version of this MIB file.

h3cVoCallHistory.contactinfo: Platform Team H3C Technologies Co., Ltd. Hai-Dian District Beijing P.R. China Http://www.h3c.com Zip:100085
h3cVoCallHistory.description: This MIB file is to provide the definition of voice call history record information.

H3cGUid.name: H3cGUid
H3cGUid.description: Represents a global call identifier. The global call identifier is used as a unique identifier for an end-to-end call. A zero length H3cGUid indicates no value for the global call identifier.

h3cCallHistoryTable.name: h3cCallHistoryTable
h3cCallHistoryTable.description: A table containing information about specific calls to a specific destination.

h3cCallHistoryEntry.name: h3cCallHistoryEntry
h3cCallHistoryEntry.description: The information regarding a single connection.

h3cCallHistoryIndex.name: h3cCallHistoryIndex
h3cCallHistoryIndex.description: The index of the call history table. It's a monotonically increasing integer for the sole purpose of indexing call disconnection events. When it reaches to the maximum value, the value will back to 1.

h3cCallHistorySetupTime.name: h3cCallHistorySetupTime
h3cCallHistorySetupTime.description: The value of sysUpTime when the call was started.

h3cCallHistoryConnectTime.name: h3cCallHistoryConnectTime
h3cCallHistoryConnectTime.description: The value of sysUpTime when the call was connected. If the call is not connected, this object will have a value of zero.

h3cCallHistoryTerminateTime.name: h3cCallHistoryTerminateTime
h3cCallHistoryTerminateTime.description: The value of sysUpTime when the call was terminated.

h3cCallHistoryPeerAddress.name: h3cCallHistoryPeerAddress
h3cCallHistoryPeerAddress.description: The number this call was connected to. If the number is not available, it will have a length of zero.

h3cCallHistoryPeerId.name: h3cCallHistoryPeerId
h3cCallHistoryPeerId.description: This object identifies a single peer. This is the Id value of the peer table entry to which this call was made. If a peer table entry for this call does not exist or is unknown, the value of this object will be zero.

h3cCallHistoryLogicalIfIndex.name: h3cCallHistoryLogicalIfIndex
h3cCallHistoryLogicalIfIndex.description: This is the ifIndex value of the logical interface through which this call was made. For ISDN media, this would be the ifIndex of the B channel which was used for this call. If the ifIndex value is unknown, the value of this object will be zero.

h3cCallHistoryCallOrigin.name: h3cCallHistoryCallOrigin
h3cCallHistoryCallOrigin.description: The call origin. originate The call that is initiated. answer The call that is accepted. callback Either rejects the call and then calls back, or uses the 'Reverse charging' information element if it is available. Note that callback(3) is supposed to control charging, not security, and applies to callback prior to accepting a call. Callback for security reasons can be handled using PPP callback.

h3cCallHistoryChargedUnits.name: h3cCallHistoryChargedUnits
h3cCallHistoryChargedUnits.description: The number of charged units for this connection. For incoming calls or if charging information is not supplied by the switch, the value of this object will be zero.

h3cCallHistoryInfoType.name: h3cCallHistoryInfoType
h3cCallHistoryInfoType.description: The information type for this call. other E.g. for non-isdn media. speech Speech. unrestrictedDigital Unrestricted digital information with 64k rate adaption. unrestrictedDigital56 Unrestricted digital information with 56k rate adaption. restrictedDigital Restricted digital information. audio31 3.1 kHz audio. audio7 7 kHz audio. video Video. packetSwitched Packetswitch. fax Fax.

h3cCallHistoryTransmitPackets.name: h3cCallHistoryTransmitPackets
h3cCallHistoryTransmitPackets.description: The number of packets which were transmitted while this call was active.

h3cCallHistoryTransmitBytes.name: h3cCallHistoryTransmitBytes
h3cCallHistoryTransmitBytes.description: The number of bytes which were transmitted for this call.

h3cCallHistoryReceivePackets.name: h3cCallHistoryReceivePackets
h3cCallHistoryReceivePackets.description: The number of packets which were received for this call.

h3cCallHistoryReceiveBytes.name: h3cCallHistoryReceiveBytes
h3cCallHistoryReceiveBytes.description: The number of bytes which were received for this call.

h3cVoiceCallHistoryTable.name: h3cVoiceCallHistoryTable
h3cVoiceCallHistoryTable.description: This table is the voice extension to the call history table of DIAL-CONTROL-MIB. It contains voice encapsulation call leg information that is derived from the statistics of lower layer telephony interface.

h3cVoiceCallHistoryEntry.name: h3cVoiceCallHistoryEntry
h3cVoiceCallHistoryEntry.description: The information regarding a extended voice call history information.

h3cVoCallHistoryConnectionId.name: h3cVoCallHistoryConnectionId
h3cVoCallHistoryConnectionId.description: The global call identifier of circuit switched network for the gateway call.

h3cVoCallHistoryTxDuration.name: h3cVoCallHistoryTxDuration
h3cVoCallHistoryTxDuration.description: Duration of transmit path open from this peer to the voice gateway for the call. The units is milliseconds.

h3cVoCallHistoryVoiceTxDuration.name: h3cVoCallHistoryVoiceTxDuration
h3cVoCallHistoryVoiceTxDuration.description: Duration of voice transmitted from this peer to voice gateway for this call. The voice utilization rate can be obtained by dividing this by h3cVoCallHistoryTxDuration object. The units is milliseconds.

h3cVoCallHistoryFaxTxDuration.name: h3cVoCallHistoryFaxTxDuration
h3cVoCallHistoryFaxTxDuration.description: Duration of fax transmitted from this peer to voice gateway for this call. The fax utilization rate can be obtained by dividing this by h3cVoCallHistoryTxDuration object. The units is milliseconds.

h3cVoCallHistoryCoderType.name: h3cVoCallHistoryCoderType
h3cVoCallHistoryCoderType.description: The negotiated coder type. It specifies the encode type to the PSTN leg of a call.

h3cVoCallHistoryImgPageCount.name: h3cVoCallHistoryImgPageCount
h3cVoCallHistoryImgPageCount.description: The number of fax related image pages are received or transmitted via the peer for the call. The units is page.

h3cVoiceVoIPCallHistoryTable.name: h3cVoiceVoIPCallHistoryTable
h3cVoiceVoIPCallHistoryTable.description: This table is the VoIP extension to the call active table of DIAL-CONTROL-MIB. It contains VoIP call leg information about specific VoIP call destination.

h3cVoiceVoIPCallHistoryEntry.name: h3cVoiceVoIPCallHistoryEntry
h3cVoiceVoIPCallHistoryEntry.description: The information regarding a extended VoIP call history information.

h3cVoVoIPCallHistoryConnectionId.name: h3cVoVoIPCallHistoryConnectionId
h3cVoVoIPCallHistoryConnectionId.description: The global call identifier of packet-switched network for the gateway call.

h3cVoVoIPCallHistoryRemSigIPType.name: h3cVoVoIPCallHistoryRemSigIPType
h3cVoVoIPCallHistoryRemSigIPType.description: The type of remote system signalling IP address for the VoIP call.

h3cVoVoIPCallHistoryRemSigIPAddr.name: h3cVoVoIPCallHistoryRemSigIPAddr
h3cVoVoIPCallHistoryRemSigIPAddr.description: Remote system signalling IP address for the VoIP call.

h3cVoVoIPCallHistoryRemSigPort.name: h3cVoVoIPCallHistoryRemSigPort
h3cVoVoIPCallHistoryRemSigPort.description: Remote system UDP listener signalling port to which to transmit voice packets.

h3cVoVoIPCallHistoryRemMedIPType.name: h3cVoVoIPCallHistoryRemMedIPType
h3cVoVoIPCallHistoryRemMedIPType.description: The type of remote system media IP address for the VoIP call.

h3cVoVoIPCallHistoryRemMedIPAddr.name: h3cVoVoIPCallHistoryRemMedIPAddr
h3cVoVoIPCallHistoryRemMedIPAddr.description: Remote system media IP address for the VoIP call.

h3cVoVoIPCallHistoryRemMedPort.name: h3cVoVoIPCallHistoryRemMedPort
h3cVoVoIPCallHistoryRemMedPort.description: Remote system UDP listener media port to which to transmit voice packets.

h3cVoVoIPCallHistorySessProtocol.name: h3cVoVoIPCallHistorySessProtocol
h3cVoVoIPCallHistorySessProtocol.description: The object specifies the session protocol to be used for internet call between local and remote router via IP backbone. unknown The protocol is unknown. h323 The protocol is H323. sip The protocol is session initiation.

h3cVoVoIPCallHistoryCoderType.name: h3cVoVoIPCallHistoryCoderType
h3cVoVoIPCallHistoryCoderType.description: The negotiated coder type. It specifies the encode type to the VoIP leg of a call.
